entries.text: Value indicating the general strength of one's combined attributes. Use souls to level up.
Total souls in possession. Souls have various uses, but are left behind at the spot of one's death.
Required number of souls to level up. Leveling up raises an attribute.
The degree to which this character is cursed. The character will turn hollow if the curse grows too severe.
Attribute governing HP. Also governs resistance to frost.
Attribute governing stamina. Also governs resistance to lightning and bleeding.
Attribute governing FP. Also determines number of attunement slots.
Attribute required to wield powerful and heavy weapons. Also governs resistance to fire and improves attack strength.
Attribute required to wield advanced weapons. Also improves attack strength, reduces spellcasting time, and reduces damage taken when falling.
Attribute governing physical defense, though this is also affected by other attributes. Also governs maximum equip load and poison resistance.
Attribute required to cast sorceries and pyromancies. Increases spell potency. (Pyromancy is affected by both faith and intelligence.) Magic defense is also calculated from this attribute.
Attribute required to cast miracles and pyromancies. Increases spell potency. (Pyromancy is affected by both faith and intelligence.) Dark defense is also calculated from this attribute.
Attribute governing item discovery. Ups bleeding and poison capabilities. Also governs resistance to curses.
One's mettle, or will to live. Character dies when this reaches zero. Use the Estus Flask, or rest at a bonfire to replenish.
Required to use spells and Skills. Use the Ashen Estus Flask, or rest at a bonfire to replenish.
Required for various actions. Depletes when actions are taken, but recovers automatically.
Total weight of equipped weapons and armor. Movement slows as load increases. Exceed the rightmost number and movement slows dramatically.
Calculated by dividing overall weight of equipped armor and weapons by the max equippable load. A greater value results in slow movement. Over 100% results in extremely slow movement.
Max weight value of equippable weapons and armor. Movement slows as load increases. Exceed this number and movement slows dramatically.
Attack power of weapon equipped in right hand Slot 1
Attack power of weapon equipped in right hand Slot 2
Attack power of weapon equipped in right hand Slot 3
Attack power of weapon equipped in left hand Slot 1
Attack power of weapon equipped in left hand Slot 2
Attack power of weapon equipped in left hand Slot 3
Character's defense against standard physical attacks
Character's defense against striking physical attacks
Character's defense against slashing physical attacks
Character's defense against thrusting physical attacks
Character's resistance to various poisons. The higher this value, the longer one can resist poisoning.
Character's resistance to bleed effect. The higher this value, the longer one can resist bleeding.
Character's resistance to curse effect. The higher this value, the longer one can resist being cursed.
Character's resistance to frost. The higher this value, the longer one can resist frostbite.
Number of attunement slots for spells. Spells take the form of sorceries, pyromancies, and miracles.
Governs likelihood of finding items on the corpses of defeated foes
Defense against and absorption of standard physical damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of striking physical damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of slashing physical damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of thrusting physical damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of magic damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of fire damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of lightning damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Defense against and absorption of dark damage. Defense is calculated by character attributes, and absorption is the combined value of all equipped armor and additional effects.
Combined total value of all equipped armor's resistance to various poisons. The higher this value, the more difficult it is to become poisoned.
Combined total value of all equipped armor's resistance to bleeding. The higher this value, the more difficult it is to start bleeding.
Combined total value of all equipped armor's resistance to curse effect. The higher this value, the more difficult it is to become cursed.
Combined total value of all equipped armor's resistance to frostbite. The higher this value, the more difficult it is to get frostbite.
Weapon category. Weapons belonging to the same category exhibit similar properties.
Spell category. Spells take the form of sorceries, pyromancies, and miracles.
The types of physical damage inflicted by a weapon. Other than standard physical damage, strike, slash or thrust damage can also be dealt.
Number of this item currently held. The rightmost number indicates the maximum you may hold at one time.
Number of this item in storage. The rightmost number indicates the maximum you may hold at one time.
Types of Skill you may perform. Performing Skills consumes FP.

Determines power of critical attacks such as backstabs and ripostes after parrying
The stability of player defense. The higher this value, the smaller the amount of stamina consumed when guarding attacks.
Degree to which spells are strengthened. Spells take the form of sorceries, pyromancies, and miracles.
Amount of FP consumed by performing a Skill
Number of slots required to attune spell
Amount of FP consumed by casting spell
Poison effect's strength. The higher this value, the quicker the poison will take effect.
Bleed effect's strength. The higher this value, the quicker the bleeding will come into effect.
Frost effect's strength. The higher this value, the quicker the frostbite will come into effect.

Resistance to frost. The higher this value, the longer one can resist frostbite.
